Nasarawa State governor, Engineer Abdullahi Sule, has called on members of opposition political parties to join hands with his administration towards developing the state. Hosting chairmen of the 13 local government areas in the state, he called on every citizen of the state, including members of the opposition political parties, to join him and work together for the development of the state. “Therefore, I am using the opportunity to call on all good people of Nasarawa, irrespective of religion, age or political affiliations, to come together so we can develop our state,” he said. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY He recalled that on receiving the news of his victory at the tribunal, he immediately reached out to David Ombugadu of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), urging him to see the judgement as victory for all. Zamfara Governor-elect seeks opposition’s cooperation to develop the state No plan to sack LG chairmen, says Nasarawa governor Wadada faces daunting task to succeed Almakura